{
  "texts": [
    "ReSKGC (Yu and Yang, 2023) proposes the integration of retrieval augmentation techniques with knowledge graph completion.",
    "This integration entails the selection of semantically relevant triples from the knowledge graph and their utilization as evidence to inform the generation of output through explicit reasoning.",
    "This model employs data from the Wiki-data5M and WikiKG90Mv2 datasets, demonstrating superior performance compared to other existing work in a range of conditions.",
    "Commonsense Reasoning is a challenging task for language models.",
    "In addition to exhibiting humanlike thinking and reasoning patterns, these models must also be able to store a substantial amount of commonsense knowledge."
  ]
}